'''''Ancient Aliens''''' is an American television series that premiered on April 20, 2010, on the [[History (U.S. TV channel)|History]] channel.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.history.com/shows/ancient-aliens/episodes|title=Ancient Aliens Episode Guide|date=December 25, 2010|publisher=History.com}}</ref> Produced by [[Prometheus Entertainment]] in a documentary style, the program presents hypotheses of [[ancient astronauts]] and proposes that historical texts, archaeology, and legends contain evidence of past human-[[Potential cultural impact of extraterrestrial contact|extraterrestrial contact]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.history.com/shows/ancient-aliens/articles/ancient-alien-theory|title=Ancient Aliens Theory|date=December 25, 2010|publisher=History.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.history.com/shows/ancient-aliens/articles/evidence-of-ancient-aliens|title=Evidence of Ancient Aliens?|date=December 25, 2010|publisher=History.com}}</ref> The show has been widely criticized by [[historians]], [[cosmologists]] and other scientific circles for presenting and promoting [[pseudoscience]] and [[pseudohistory]].

The series started with a [[TV special]] of the same name that aired on March 8, 2009, on the [[History (U.S. TV channel)|History]] channel. Seasons 1–3 aired on the same channel until 2011. From season 4 to the middle of season 7, the series aired on [[H2 (TV channel)|H2]]. On April 10, 2015, episode premieres returned to History.

Season 13 premiered on April 27, 2018 with a two-hour special.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.monstersandcritics.com/smallscreen/ancient-aliens-season-13-when-will-show-return|title=Ancient Aliens Season 13: What date will show return in 2018?|first=Julian|last=Cheetle|publisher=Monstersandcritics.com|date=March 30, 2018|accessdate=April 28, 2018}}</ref>

==Production==
The executive producer of ''Ancient Aliens'' is [[Kevin Burns]], who also directed and wrote the pilot episode. [[Giorgio A. Tsoukalos]] serves as consulting producer and appeared on screen in the pilot.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://radioamerikanow.com/?p=1731|title=December 4, 2010, Giorgio Tsoukalos, "Ancient Aliens" & "Twilight of the Gods"|author=Barb|format=podcast|publisher=Radio Amerika Now|date=December 4, 2010|accessdate=June 20, 2011}}</ref> [[Erich von Däniken]] appeared in the pilot episode, and UFO researcher [[C. Scott Littleton]] served as an expert consultant for the show until his death in 2010.<ref>{{cite journal|doi=10.1111/j.1556-3502.2011.52231.x|title=Obituary of C. Scott Littleton|work=Anthropology News|date=February 17, 2011|volume=52|number=2|pages=31–32}}</ref>

Radio talk show host [[George Noory]] speaks in five episodes, including the pilot. Reverend [[Barry Downing]], known for describing angels in the Bible as ancient astronauts, offered his viewpoints in the pilot episode. Psychologist [[Jonathan Young (psychologist)|Jonathan Young]], who brings a mythological perspective, appears on screen in every episode but the first pilot. [[Alternate history]] author [[David Hatcher Childress]] speaks frequently in most episodes.

