{{BLP sources|date=June 2011}} [[Image:Bohdan Osadczuk 02.JPG|right|200px|thumb|'''Bohdan Osadchuk''']] [[Image:Bohdan Osadczuk 01.JPG|right|200px|thumb|'''Bohdan Osadchuk''', Krynica-Zdrój ([[Poland]]), September 8, 2005]] ''' Bohdan Osadchuk ''' (1 August 1920 – 19 October 2011) was a Ukrainian historian and journalist.<ref>[http://www.centrum.umcs.pl/en/about-us/history College history] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110912025445/http://www.centrum.umcs.pl/en/about-us/history |date=September 12, 2011 }}</ref>
Dr. Bohdan Osadchuk was born in [[Kolomyia]]. He was a professor at the [[Free University of Berlin]], one of the most senior members of the Ukrainian Free University (UFU) of Munich, and a long-standing freelance writer for ''Kultura'', a Polish emigre magazine published in Paris (editor [[Jerzy Giedroyc]]). In 2009 he was awarded a ''[[Bene Merito]]'' Honour medal by Foreign Minister [[Radosław Sikorski]] ''in recognition of scientific achievements and efforts to Polish-Ukrainian reconciliation.''<ref>[http://www.msz.gov.pl/Wreczenie,przez,ministra,Radoslawa,Sikorskiego,odznaki,Bene,Merito,31431.html Wręczenie przez ministra Radosława Sikorskiego odznaki Bene Merito] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110813134716/http://www.msz.gov.pl/Wreczenie%2Cprzez%2Cministra%2CRadoslawa%2CSikorskiego%2Codznaki%2CBene%2CMerito%2C31431.html |date=August 13, 2011 }}</ref>
He died in [[Czechówka, Lesser Poland Voivodeship|Czechówka]] near [[Myślenice]] situated in the [[Lesser Poland Voivodeship]].
