{{Moroccan literature}} '''Tuhami al-Wazzani''' (1903–1972) was a [[Morocco|Moroccan]] historian from [[Tétouan]].<ref>M’hammad Benaboud, ''Tetouan, its History and Culture'', p. 2</ref> He is especially well known for his autobiography ''Al-Zawiyya''.<ref>''Al-Zawiyya'', Tetouan, Muassasat al-Tuhami al-Wazzani li al-Taqafa wa al-Nachr, 1999 (First edition published by Matbaat al-Rif, 1942)</ref> This book was first published in episodes in the magazine ''Al-Rif'' (founded by him August 27, 1936), beginning in 1939. Al-Wazzani translated Cervantes' [[Don Quixote]] into Arabic.
==References== <references/> *Francisco Rodríguez Sierra, "Apuntes para un acercamiento sistémico a la obra de Tuhami al-Wazzani: la zagüía entre la autobiografía y la novela", in: Al-Andalus Magreb: Estudios árabes e islámicos, {{ISSN|1133-8571}}, Nº 12, 2005, pags. 129-146 *Francisco Rodríguez Sierra, "La traducción del Quijote al árabe del tetuaní Tuhami al-Wazzani", in: Don Quijote por tierras extranjeras: Estudios sobre la recepción internacional de la novela cervantina / coord. por Hans Christian Hagedorn, 2007, {{ISBN|978-84-8427-448-3}}, pags. 141-152
